@NODE Introduction "Cloanto - The Kara Collection - Introduction"
@TOC Main

@{B}Introduction@{UB}

It took 10 years of hard work to create the superb art which is contained
on this CD-ROM. The Kara Collection includes all packages previously
published by Kara Computer Graphics for the Amiga, in an exclusive and
professional edition reorganized and enhanced by Cloanto. Some material is
being published here for the very first time.

This CD-ROM contains 80 ColorFonts (including effects like brick, glass,
chrome, chisel, etc.), 5 AnimFonts (handwriting, rotating characters,
static wipes, sparkles, etc.), hundreds of alternate color palettes,
Starfields (moving stars seen from different perspectives), Plaquegrounds
(backgrounds such as granite, marble, sand-stone, wood, etc.), and
software for special effects in pictures, animations, titling and
presentations. All items for solo or combined use.

The Kara Collection also includes two software packages developed by
Cloanto to manage bitmapped fonts: ColorType for color fonts and the
Personal Fonts Maker for black and white fonts. Both have been acclaimed
as the best in their respective fields.

To make AnimFonts really easy and enjoyable to use, we created an ARexx
program for Personal Paint, which renders any string of characters into
animated text. As Kara says, "So long to the laborious task of placing
individual letters... This is the way AnimFonts were meant to be!!!"

For users who already purchased a copy of Personal Paint, but in a version
which does not support anim-brushes (which are required to use AnimFonts),
this CD-ROM includes a free upgrade. A demonstration version of Personal
Paint is also supplied.

The Amiga has been through difficult times, and so have we, developers and
users. Yet we have kept working for the Amiga, and you are still here too,
with one of our creations. We will not forget these times, and we hope
that you are enjoying them too.

Thank you.

@{I}The Cloanto Team @{UI}


@{B}Introduction by Kara@{UB}

Thank you for purchasing The Kara Collection. I would like to share with
you some memories I have of making the fonts and the other artwork
contained in this CD-ROM.

In 1987, I quit my Graphic Design position to venture out into video (so I
thought!) until repeated interviewers kept saying I should check out
computer graphics. Finally, someone said "Check out the Amiga". I did and
invested in the Amiga 1000. God, was I excited! (I'm sure you can relate
to that excitement when you first got your Amiga!) I would sit in front of
the screen so long that when I closed my eyes, I could still see the
criss-cross of the monitor screen. (Perhaps I was a little too close, but
if you want to be intimate, you have to be close!) I started to learn by
giving myself objects to make (objects like a @{" Chrome Apple " SYSTEM "Execute KARACDROOT:Utilities/H/2/ShowPic KARACDROOT:Pictures/Chrome_Apple.pic"},
@{" Strawberry " SYSTEM "Execute KARACDROOT:Utilities/H/2/ShowPic KARACDROOT:Pictures/Strawberry.pic"}, @{" Eight Ball " SYSTEM "Execute KARACDROOT:Utilities/H/2/ShowPic KARACDROOT:Pictures/Eight_Ball.pic"}, @{" Lips " SYSTEM "Execute KARACDROOT:Utilities/H/2/ShowPic KARACDROOT:Pictures/Lips.pic"}), learning new effects each time. From
the beginning, I was unhappy with the font selection so I started making
my own. Since I was on a computer, I thought that they should be
dimensional and that's when Kara Fonts were born! I started doing fonts
with different kinds of effects that appealed to me. Whenever I showed
Amiga people what I was doing, they always said that they would like to
have them. Then came Calligrapher to allow me to put the letters into the
keyboard and that's how Kara Fonts came into being. (Note: Calligrapher
from Inter/Active Softworks is not in business any more. But you can do it
with ColorType from Cloanto!)

In the last ten years of designing and rendering these fonts, I've worn
out four mice, countless number of mouse pads, one Amiga, five disk
drives, two monitors, one tattered chair and a weary set of eyes. All for
the enjoyment of detailing, nit-picking, pixel moving, pixel changing, and
colorizing my "babies". (That's exactly how I saw them.) Like most
artists, I made things that I enjoy (why not!!) I also remember staying up
at late night trying to figure out how to get a certain effect. I would
get to the point of giving up thinking about it when a quiet voice inside
my head would suggest a certain direction, I, automatically, would
acknowledge with an "O.K.", do what I was told and laugh with joy when it
worked! So, there is a lot of joy in these fonts. I hope that they give
you joy like I had making them.

Enjoy!

@{I}Kara @{UI}


@{B}The Future@{UB}

With your support, we are continuing to invest in the Amiga. We are
working on new versions of our software, and we are publishing new CD-ROM
titles such as the @{" Personal Suite " LINK PSuite}.

We are currently working on a set of ARexx programs and software
extensions which will allow Personal Paint to interact with ColorType in
incredible and exciting new ways. For example, it will be possible to
apply image processing and textures to existing fonts. Amiga vector fonts
can then be used to automatically create ColorFonts in any size. The
required ARexx interface is already in ColorType, on this CD-ROM!

To create new and better software we also need your help. Please let us
have your suggestions.


