@{B}Using The Kara Collection@{UB}

Before using The Kara Collection, please double-click on one of the
language configuration icons (for example "English"). This tells the
system where certain programs and preinstalled fonts are to be loaded
from, and allows all applications to run smoothly from The Kara
Collection. If software and documentation exist in the selected language,
these are also configured accordingly.

An automatic installation program is included in the "Utilities" drawer of
the CD-ROM. Using this procedure guarantees that software is installed in
the desired language, and that data files optimized for size (rather than
for CD-ROM performance) are copied, thereby saving hard disk space. Manual
installation is also possible: all software titles, font files and other
artwork on this CD-ROM can be installed to hard disk by simply dragging
the corresponding drawer out of the CD-ROM window and dropping it on the
hard drive. The Amiga Workbench displays a message if there is not enough
space to copy the complete drawer.

We appreciate the fact that most users handle their CD-ROMs with great
care, but we also want you to feel free to use The Kara Collection as
often as you like. If you damage your CD-ROM during the first two years of
normal use, you can send it back to us in a self-addressed envelope, and
we will replace it at no cost to you (with a CD-ROM having the same
