@NODE PPaint "Cloanto - The Kara Collection - Personal Paint"
@TOC Main

@{B}Cloanto Personal Paint@{UB}

Personal Paint is a powerful and intuitive paint, image processing,
animation and 24-bit printing package. Employ stunning effects like
emboss, water-colors, transparencies and stereograms (as in "Magic Eye"),
while virtual memory frees precious Chip RAM by using other storage
resources! Plus: support of RTG graphics cards, different file formats
(IFF, PNG, PCX, C source code, DataTypes, etc.), nine brushes, two
independent working environments, multi-level Undo/Redo, animation
storyboard, Bézier curves, autoscroll painting, Internet publishing
features (professional color reduction, transparency and progressive
display), superior text editor, color fonts, PostScript output, screen
grabber...


@{B}Personal Paint Demo@{UB}

The Kara Collection includes a demonstration version of Personal Paint,
which is used as a default viewer to display images and animations on the
CD-ROM. This version of Personal Paint even saves and prints, and
therefore can be used to completely explore the features of the full
program. The only limitation compared to the commercial version is that a
"DEMO" pattern covers parts of the image when certain operation are
performed. The full product also includes extensive documentation (either
in print or on CD-ROM).

The Kara Collection does not include the full version of Personal Paint.
The program is available either separately, or in the Personal Suite
CD-ROM. The demonstration version on this CD-ROM may not be representative
of the latest version of Personal Paint.


@{B}Personal Paint Upgrade@{UB}

Certain sections of The Kara Collection (AnimFonts and Starfields) make
use of anim-brushes, which are not supported by all versions of Personal
Paint. For users of these older versions of Personal Paint, the CD-ROM
includes a free anim-brush upgrade. The upgrade can be installed to the
hard disk with the normal installation procedure ("Utilities" drawer), and
it requires an older version of the program to be already installed. The
upgrade will not work on demo or cover disk versions, or on compressed
executable files (unless compressed with Imploder). Executable Personal
Paint files compressed with PowerPacker or similar utilities must be
decompressed before being upgraded. The installation and upgrade procedure
also asks for the original Personal Paint or Personal Suite serial number
in order to determine the exact version of the old program. The anim-brush
extensions are not installed over newer versions of Personal Paint which
already support anim-brushes. It is strongly recommended to make a backup
copy of the drawer containing the old version of Personal Paint, in order
to preserve that environment, which may remain of interest even after the
upgrade.

The free upgrade is included mainly to support the features documented in
this CD-ROM. The full package and various commercial upgrades include
additional documentation.


